NAME platform-benchmarks
PURPOSE
A number without a benchmark is meaningless. "3% engagement" is excellent for a 500K account and weak for a 2K account. These benchmarks are calibrated to YVON's venture scale — not industry averages for brands 10× the size. 
--- 
INSTAGRAM — NOVIZIO (~9K FOLLOWERS, FASHION/EDITORIAL)
Metric Below average Average Good Strong Engagement rate (likes+comments / followers) < 1% 1–2% 2–4% > 4% Reach rate per post (reach / followers) < 15% 15–30% 30–50% > 50% Story completion rate < 60% 60–75% 75–85% > 85% Follower growth (WoW) < 0.5% 0.5–1% 1–2% > 2% Saves per post / reach < 0.5% 0.5–1% 1–3% > 3% 
Novizio context: Fashion editorial accounts at this scale should target 2–4% engagement. Saves are a stronger signal than likes — saves indicate purchase intent for fashion content. 
--- 
YOUTUBE — NOVIZIO / HOURBOUR (EARLY-STAGE, < 5K SUBSCRIBERS)
Metric Below average Average Good Strong Click-through rate (CTR) < 2% 2–4% 4–7% > 7% Average view duration (retention) < 30% 30–45% 45–60% > 60% Subscriber conversion rate (subs / views) < 0.5% 0.5–1% 1–3% > 3% 
YT context: First 24–48h after upload spike views and distort retention — do not benchmark from the first week. Use 7-day settled data. 
--- 
LINKEDIN — HOURBOUR (B2B SAAS, EARLY-STAGE)
Metric Below average Average Good Strong Post impressions / follower count < 3× 3–8× 8–15× > 15× Engagement rate (reactions+comments / impressions) < 1% 1–3% 3–5% > 5% Follower growth (MoM) < 1% 1–3% 3–6% > 6% CTR on link posts < 0.5% 0.5–1% 1–2% > 2% 
LinkedIn context: LinkedIn's algorithm heavily boosts early engagement (first 60 min). Impressions can be inflated by algorithmic distribution — weight comments and saves more than impressions. 
--- 
GOOGLE ANALYTICS 4 — NOVIZIO (E-COMMERCE)
Metric Below average Average Good Strong Bounce rate (engagement rate inverse) > 70% 55–70% 40–55% < 40% Session duration < 1 min 1–2 min 2–4 min > 4 min Pages per session < 1.5 1.5–2.5 2.5–4 > 4 Conversion rate (purchase) < 0.5% 0.5–1.5% 1.5–3% > 3% 
--- 
GA4 — HOURBOUR (SAAS LANDING + APP)
Metric Below average Average Good Strong Bounce rate > 65% 50–65% 35–50% < 35% Trial signup rate (landing → trial) < 1% 1–3% 3–7% > 7% Session duration (pricing/product pages) < 1.5 min 1.5–3 min 3–5 min > 5 min 
--- 
SCALE MATCHING RULE
Before citing any competitor benchmark: 
Novizio competitors must be < 50K followers. Do not benchmark against 200K+ fashion brands. Hourbour competitors must be early-stage SaaS (< $500K ARR equivalent scale) or explicitly labeled "aspirational benchmark." Violating this rule produces misleading gap analysis. A gap that can't be closed at current scale is not actionable. 
--- 
BENCHMARK REFRESH
These benchmarks should be validated quarterly via WebSearch. Platform algorithms change — benchmarks from 12+ months ago may not reflect current organic reach norms. 
LAST_VALIDATED 2026-05-20.